# FinTech-LLM Environment Variables Configuration

This project uses a `.env` file to manage configuration and API keys. This file should be placed in the project root directory.

## Required API Keys

- `OPENAI_API_KEY`: Your OpenAI API key for GPT model access
- `GEMINI_API_KEY`: Your Google Gemini API key for Gemini model access  
- `GROQ_API_KEY`: Your GroQ API key for GroQ model access

## Configuration Options

- `LLM_PROVIDER`: The LLM provider to use (options: `openai`, `gemini`, `groq`)
- `GEMINI_MODEL`: The specific Gemini model to use (default: `gemini-2.5-pro-exp-0827`)
- `OPENAI_MODEL`: The specific OpenAI model to use (default: `gpt-4-turbo-preview`)
- `GROQ_MODEL`: The specific GroQ model to use (default: `llama3-8b-8192`)

## Optional Configuration

- `PINECONE_API_KEY`: Pinecone API key for vector storage (optional)
- `PINECONE_ENVIRONMENT`: Pinecone environment (default: `us-east1-gcp`)
- `DATABASE_URL`: Database connection string (default: local SQLite)
- `REDIS_URL`: Redis connection string (default: local Redis)
- `SECRET_KEY`: Secret key for authentication (randomly generated if not set)
- `MONGODB_URL`: MongoDB connection string (default: `mongodb://localhost:27017`)
- `MONGODB_DB_NAME`: MongoDB database name (default: `fintech_llm`)
- `CHATS_COLLECTION_NAME`: MongoDB collection name for chats (default: `chats`)

## Processing Configuration

- `CHUNK_SIZE`: Size of text chunks for processing (default: 1000)
- `CHUNK_OVERLAP`: Overlap between text chunks (default: 200)
- `MAX_FILE_SIZE`: Maximum file size in bytes (default: 50MB)
- `SIMILARITY_THRESHOLD`: Threshold for similarity matching (default: 0.3)

## File Extensions

- `ALLOWED_EXTENSIONS`: Comma-separated list of allowed file extensions (default: `.pdf,.docx,.txt,.eml`)